{{Year in Sri Lanka|2003}}

The following lists events that happened during '''2003 in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[Ranil Wickremesinghe]]. 
==Events==
*Tropical cyclone ''Very Severe Cyclonic Storm BOB 01''<ref>{{cite report|publisher=[[National Hurricane Center]]|date=2015-09-09|title=Worldwide Tropical Cyclone Centers|accessdate=2012-08-27|url=http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/aboutrsmc.shtml}}</ref>  takes aim at [[Sri Lanka]] making landfall on 16 May 2003, the storm produced record amounts of rainfall and led to severe flooding in more low elevation areas of the nation. The storm would end up displacing 800,000 residents as a result of the severe flooding.<ref name="imd">{{cite journal|journal=MAUSAM|volume=55|number=3|date=July 2004|title=Cyclones and depressions over north Indian Ocean during 2003|author=N. Jayanthi|author2=A. B. Mazumdar|author3=S. Sunitha Devi|accessdate=2015-09-09|url=http://www.imdchennai.gov.in/Mausamcw/2003.pdf|format=PDF}}</ref>
*On October 2003, the [[LTTE]] issues a proposal known as the [[Interim Self Governing Authority]]. Once approved, it will assure the LTTE governance of the eastern areas of Sri Lanka, getting them closer to establishing a ''[[Tamil Eelam]]'' (a state in which is separate from Sri Lanka itself). <ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/south_asia/3232913.stm Full text of LTTE's ISGA proposals BBC News November 2003]</ref>
